{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LtVnPkSnSw3GT8Busdd1PV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The raylet is running on the ray-client pod. The `ray start` command I executed is running as a background daemon with PID 147 (raylet process). This will persist as long as the pod is alive.\n\nBut there's an issue: this `ray start` was initiated by `kubectl exec`, which means when the exec session ended, the process stayed alive (because `ray start` forks and runs in background). The raylet process (PID 147) is owned by the `ray` user and is independent of any shell session.\n\nThe validation is working now. Let me summarize what happened:\nI deployed the ray-head and ray-worker deployments with their services, then hit a snag when trying to connect—the Python client needed a local raylet running first, but the automatic subprocess startup was failing due to environment issues. So I manually started the raylet daemon on the ray-client pod pointing to the ray-head service, and now the connection works.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3002,"cache_read_input_tokens":40654,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3002},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19f3b609-fb9f-42d7-bf77-90a95f6e0a7e","uuid":"60afb0c8-8eb7-46ad-b593-87e48be1eae9","request_id":"req_011Cc6rLxBaU5Q6ovBExYEvg"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LtVnPkSnSw3GT8Busdd1PV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Deployed:**\n- `ray-head` Deployment (1 replica) — `rayproject/ray:2.9.0`, starts GCS on port 6379\n- `ray-head` Service — routes port 6379 to the head pod\n- `ray-worker` Deployment (2 replicas) — connects to `ray-head:6379`\n\n**Issue encountered:** In Ray 2.9.0, `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` (GCS/driver mode) requires a local raylet already running on the calling pod. The ray-client pod's `sleep infinity` command doesn't start one, so I ran `ray start --address=ray-head:6379 --num-cpus=0` directly in the pod to join the cluster as a node. The raylet daemon (PID 147) persists inside the pod independently.\n\n**Validation output:**\n```\nConnecting to existing Ray cluster at address: ray-head:6379...\nConnected to Ray cluster.\nok\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3002,"cache_read_input_tokens":40654,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3002},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19f3b609-fb9f-42d7-bf77-90a95f6e0a7e","uuid":"53a4c0af-4bf4-4577-922c-9e59401f8718","request_id":"req_011Cc6rLxBaU5Q6ovBExYEvg"}
